00:04:22.290 --> 00:04:24.490
What does that look like,
a successful pride event?

00:04:24.490 --> 00:04:26.460
MATT BEARD: So a
successful pride event

00:04:26.460 --> 00:04:29.220
in a hostile
environment, firstly, it

00:04:29.220 --> 00:04:33.500
looks like an event
which is peaceful,

00:04:33.500 --> 00:04:37.200
where LGBT plus people
have not been physically

00:04:37.200 --> 00:04:40.260
attacked or intimidated.

00:04:40.260 --> 00:04:45.450
It is an event where the
freedom of association

00:04:45.450 --> 00:04:48.060
is guaranteed by the Universal
Declaration of Human Rights,

00:04:48.060 --> 00:04:50.820
has been respected so
that people are allowed

00:04:50.820 --> 00:04:55.500
to gather as LGBT plus people,
to be in one space at one time

00:04:55.500 --> 00:04:56.670
together.

00:04:56.670 --> 00:05:01.470
And it looks like
an event where there

00:05:01.470 --> 00:05:04.680
has been a critical mass
of people coming together.

00:05:04.680 --> 00:05:08.310
And a critical mass, in many
of the environments we work in,

00:05:08.310 --> 00:05:11.970
can be as few as 50
people, really, who

00:05:11.970 --> 00:05:15.720
can really make a difference.

00:05:15.720 --> 00:05:18.570
When I worked at Amnesty
International, 10 years ago,

00:05:18.570 --> 00:05:22.500
I took part in one of the
first prides in Riga in Latvia.

00:05:22.500 --> 00:05:24.570
And there were
literally 50 of us

00:05:24.570 --> 00:05:28.410
in that space and around
10,000 counter-protesters

00:05:28.410 --> 00:05:31.950
trying to disrupt that event.

00:05:31.950 --> 00:05:34.770
We were protected by the
police in a very efficient way,

00:05:34.770 --> 00:05:37.140
and so it remains safe.

00:05:37.140 --> 00:05:41.790
I went back 10 years later,
this summer, to Riga,

00:05:41.790 --> 00:05:43.830
and those numbers
had, basically,

00:05:43.830 --> 00:05:48.450
inverted, that there were
8,000 people participating

00:05:48.450 --> 00:05:52.740
in pride and a very sad
looking group of Nazis who

00:05:52.740 --> 00:05:55.380
were protesting against us,
probably around 50 or 60

00:05:55.380 --> 00:05:56.130
of those.

00:05:56.130 --> 00:05:58.830
So that, for me, to
answer your question,

00:05:58.830 --> 00:06:00.540
shows the progress
that can be made.

00:06:00.540 --> 00:06:02.880
From that courageous
moment 10 years ago

00:06:02.880 --> 00:06:04.680
when those Latvian
activists decided

00:06:04.680 --> 00:06:08.850
that they were going to
stand out and do this thing,

00:06:08.850 --> 00:06:11.080
despite the risks,
despite the violence,

00:06:11.080 --> 00:06:13.320
despite the intimidation,
and in 10 years

00:06:13.320 --> 00:06:16.020
they've turned that
thing around completely.

00:06:16.020 --> 00:06:19.200
And it was a joyful
occasion where, as I said,

00:06:19.200 --> 00:06:21.439
8,000 people were
able to come together.

00:06:21.439 --> 00:06:21.980
SPEAKER: Wow.

